# Trip Planner API

The Trip Planner API is a RESTful API that allows users to manage their travel plans. It provides endpoints for creating, reading, updating, and canceling trips.

## Installation

1. Clone or download the project repository.

2. Install the required dependencies using pip.

   ```bash
   pip install fastapi 
   pip install uvicorn
## Usage

    Start the server: uvicorn main:app --reload

   
Access the API documentation in your web browser:

    URL: http://localhost:8000/docs
    The documentation provides details about each endpoint and allows you to send requests directly.

API Endpoints:

    Create a new trip: Send a POST request to http://localhost:8000/trips/ with the trip details.
    Retrieve a list of trips: Send a GET request to http://localhost:8000/trips/.
    Update a trip: Send a PUT request to http://localhost:8000/trips/{trip_id} with the updated trip details.
    Replace {trip_id} with the ID of the trip you want to update.
    Cancel a trip: Send a DELETE request to http://localhost:8000/trips/{trip_id} to cancel a trip.
    Replace {trip_id} with the ID of the trip you want to cancel.

Note: Make sure to include the necessary request headers and provide the required data in the request body according to the API documentation.

## Configuration

The Trip Planner API uses a static JSON file, trips.json, to store trip information. Ensure that the file exists in the same directory as the Python script and has the correct JSON format.

